friendly /ˈfrɛndlɪ/

(friendlier,friendlies,friendliest) 

1. ADJ If someone is friendly , they behave in a pleasant, kind way, and like to be with other people. 友好的 

例： Godfrey had been friendly to me. 戈弗雷过去曾经对我是友好的。 

例： ...a man with a pleasant, friendly face. …一个和颜悦色的男子。 

2. friendliness N-UNCOUNT 友善 

例： She also loves the friendliness of the people. 她也喜爱人们的友善。 

3. ADJ If you are friendly with someone, you like each other and enjoy spending time together. 与…要好的 [v-link ADJ] 

例： I'm friendly with his mother. 我和他的母亲很要好。 

4. ADJ You can describe another country or their government as friendly when they have good relations with your own country rather than being an enemy. (国家或政府) 友好的 

例： ...a worsening in relations between the two previously friendly countries. …两个先前友好的国家之间关系的恶化。 

5. N-COUNT In sports, a friendly is a game which is not part of a competition, and is played for entertainment or practice, often without any serious effort to win. 友谊赛 [英国英语] [ADJ n] 

6. ADJ Friendly is also an adjective. 友谊赛的

